Here is what I do
hold your open hand palm side down about a beer can in height above the
grill.if you can count to five Mississippi's before you pull your hand away
the grill is hot enough.Slap your 1.5 inch thick room temperature steaks on
the grill and sprinkle with a little kosher salt.go grab a beer. don't
piddle around in the kitchen- you got food on the grill.drink the beer,flip
the meat,sprinkle with salt and go get another brewski.if you get flame ups
pour your wife's beer on the flame to put them out.
When I see the fat around the edges start to sizzle and I get about a
teaspoon of juice on the top of the steak I pull it off.get another beer let
the meat rest and then dig in
